            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 19,
              "body": "Thomas is not WELRI and not anymore UCLouvain",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:43:11Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 103,
              "body": "I would remove pre-shared key authentication from the abstract to keep draft-piraux possible",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:44:15Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 151,
              "body": "I would remove \"with a pre-shared key\". Is  MAY the right word, shouldn't is be SHOULD ?",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:45:42Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 157,
              "body": "We could already mention client certificates or MTLS in the introduction\n",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:46:17Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 158,
              "body": "replace TCP-AO -> complements TCP-AO. TCP-AO protects the TCP header, while TLS protects the TCP payload and thus the BGP messages.",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:47:32Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 162,
              "body": "Earlier you wrote MAY. We need to clearly define the words that we use",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:48:03Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 164,
              "body": "I would mention suggest. Maybe we can have two variants:\n- BOTLS with TCP-AO and preshared keys\n- BOTLS with TCP-AO and draft-piraux",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:48:49Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 187,
              "body": "A TCP connection is established on port 179. The integrity of the TCP segments is protected by using TCP-AO.",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:49:40Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 200,
              "body": "A TLS session is established over THIS TCP connection.",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:49:58Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:52Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 211,
              "body": "TCP-AO protects the integrity of the TCP header",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:50:31Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:53Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 213,
              "body": "I would remove New",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:50:40Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:53Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 215,
              "body": "We need to mention that TCP-AO is used. It becomes mandatory in this draft.",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:51:21Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:53Z"
            },
            {
              "originalPosition": 225,
              "body": "We probably need to have a section on certificates and point to this draft for this discussion.",
              "createdAt": "2026-07-01T08:51:46Z",
              "updatedAt": "2026-07-01T08:52:53Z"
            }
          ]
